at|

But sometimes you are dealt two 5 card suits ... double with 2 suits is usually a bad idea.
If the 2 suits are the lowest 2 unbid suits (e.g. you have hearts and clubs, and RHO opened 1@D) 
you might use the "unusual no trump" bid of 2NT to convey your desire to play in one of those suits

OK - Michaels cue bids are first cousin to unusual NT.
If opener starts with 1@C or 1@D, then an immediate cue bid of 2@C or 2@D promises 5-5 distribution in the MAJORS
Example: 
RHO opens 1@C and you hold  @KQ10xx  @QJxxx  @dxx  @cx 
Bid 2@C
Some people will not bid 2@C here at unfavorable vulnerability, but I am a believer in getting my bid in earlier, 
rather than later...|
