at| 

OK - Next: If your RHO opens 1@H or 1@S, a Michaels cue bid shows the other major and a (unspecified) minor
Example: 
You have  @sAJxxxx  @hx  @dKJxxx @cx and RHO opens 1@H.     Your bid is 2@H

I will get around to discussing how to find out which minor shortly
So we are clear, then, on what the Michaels cue bidder is saying when she makes a michaels cue bid
