^b@2If advancer has no tolerance for the major that the Michaels bidder has shown (and she promised a minor),
then the advancer (partner of the overcaller) bids ^*U2NT^*n conventionally ...
Asking the Michaels bidder to bid her minor.

So with the earlier example, if the auction were 1@H   2H   pass 
and advancer wants to play in the overcaller's minor, she bids 2NT

Overcaller alerts (2NT is alertable), explains that 2NT asks for opener's second suit, and then she bids it. 
In our case, that would be 3@D

You can make things a LOT more complicated, but I recommend not to - not for a while, anyway|
