OK - so one last point. 
If your pard makes a Michaels call, you are expected to bid to the Law of Total Tricks' safe level 
as soon as possible. 
Example: 
Your hand is  @sJxxx  @hxxx  @dxx  @cKxxx    Your LHO opens 1@H and your pard bids 2@H.  RHO passes 
You should bid 3@S, not 2, and you must not pass with a probable 9+ card spade fit
If you're doubled, you may be set 2 or 3 tricks, but the opps are very likely to be making game in hearts,
if not a slam.|
